summary: redrew some holly brown art the other day cuz i was watchin’ some vids on her :V commission and ko-fi in the description until i...
caption:
redrew some holly brown art the other day cuz i was watchin’ some vids on her :V

commission and ko-fi in the description until i can figure out if tumblr’s gonna fuck me over with the link thing

also, imma ramble here, but i’ve been watchin’ some critiques on her, and really i’m indifferent to her, ‘n don’t really got any input on her situation, hell i haven’t even read her comics, mmmmmbut her art, it could use some work. i’m not @ -ing her, cuz i’m not sure if she’d think i’m tryin’ to start shit, even though that’d be somewhat amusing, though i’m sure she’s had enough, but in truth, she does need to work on her art a bit more. her anatomy is p wonky, and from the comics i’ve seen in google of heres, camera poses and positioning of characters could be done a bit better, but then again i don’t draw comics fjdklfsjak.

i know i’m rambling on about advice kinda for her, but really this is for anyone, just loosen up ‘n chill out. watch some mark crilley vids, look at that one mickey mouse comic strip tutorial thing i rebloged a bit ago. i’ve heard ppl gripe about her style bein’ anime inspired, but hell, mine is too, and i never really changed it that much over the years. draw whatcha want, but draw it like you’re chill ‘n high

also, holly, if you’re readin’ this, from one 20 year old who might as well be classified as dropping out of his last 2 years of high school to another 20 something year old college kid, you’re uh…. you’re gonna need another job and have art be a side thing…… or you could do van life, which is what i wanna do, i hate bein’ in this box of a room doin’ jack shit
